The paper deals with the computational complexity of a property of games, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The use of hypergraph theory suggests a connection to discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The problem of decisiveness is related to the existence of winning coalitions, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the complexity of decision problems, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
